cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the synthesis of circuits for safety specifications, which involves logical reasoning and formal methods. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of symbolic algorithms, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The focus on safety specifications and decomposition of sub-specifications suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with formal verification, which is related to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the use of compositional algorithms for solving the synthesis problem suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
